-- Dubai's Able Logistics picks Shuaa to lead manage IPO
-- By Olzhas Auyezov
-- Sun Mar 30, 2014 03:18AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, March 30 (Reuters) - Dubai freight-forwarding company Able Logistics Group has appointed Shuaa Capital <SHUA.DU> as lead manager and bookrunner for its initial public offering later this year, the investment bank said on Sunday.

Buyout firm GrowthGate Capital plans to take Able Logistics Group public on the Dubai Financial Market around the end of 2014, GrowthGate, which owns 70 percent of Able, said earlier this month. [ID:nL6N0MH0TL] Set up in 2001, Able has annual turnover of about $200 million and operations across Gulf Arab countries and in Hong Kong. It also provides land transport and warehousing services.